var book = {
	"name": "Ecclesiastes",
	"numChapters": 12,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The words of the Teacher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17317A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17317A\"></sup> son of David, king in Jerusalem:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17317B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17317B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Meaningless! Meaningless!”says the Teacher.“Utterly meaningless!Everything is meaningless.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17318C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17318C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>What do people gain from all their laborsat which they toil under the sun?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17319D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17319D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Generations come and generations go,but the earth remains forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17320E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17320E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sun rises and the sun sets,and hurries back to where it rises.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17321F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17321F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The wind blows to the southand turns to the north;round and round it goes,ever returning on its course.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All streams flow into the sea,yet the sea is never full.To the place the streams come from,there they return again.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17323G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17323G\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All things are wearisome,more than one can say.The eye never has enough of seeing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17324H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17324H\"></sup>nor the ear its fill of hearing.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What has been will be again,what has been done will be done again;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17325I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17325I\"></sup>there is nothing new under the sun.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Is there anything of which one can say,“Look! This is something new”?It was here already, long ago;it was here before our time.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>No one remembers the former generations,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17327J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17327J\"></sup>and even those yet to comewill not be rememberedby those who follow them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17327K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17327K\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I, the Teacher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17328L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17328L\"></sup> was king over Israel in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17328M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17328M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I applied my mind to study and to explore by wisdom all that is done under the heavens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17329N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17329N\"></sup> What a heavy burden God has laid on mankind!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17329O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17329O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have seen all the things that are done under the sun; all of them are meaningless, a chasing after the wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17330P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17330P\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>What is crooked cannot be straightened;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17331Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17331Q\"></sup>what is lacking cannot be counted.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I said to myself, “Look, I have increased in wisdom more than anyone who has ruled over Jerusalem before me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17332R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17332R\"></sup> I have experienced much of wisdom and knowledge.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then I applied myself to the understanding of wisdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17333S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17333S\"></sup> and also of madness and folly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17333T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17333T\"></sup> but I learned that this, too, is a chasing after the wind.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For with much wisdom comes much sorrow;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17334U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17334U\"></sup>the more knowledge, the more grief.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17334V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17334V\"></sup>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>I said to myself, “Come now, I will test you with pleasure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17335A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17335A\"></sup> to find out what is good.” But that also proved to be meaningless.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Laughter,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17336B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17336B\"></sup> I said, “is madness. And what does pleasure accomplish?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I tried cheering myself with wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17337C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17337C\"></sup> and embracing folly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17337D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17337D\"></sup>—my mind still guiding me with wisdom. I wanted to see what was good for people to do under the heavens during the few days of their lives.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I undertook great projects: I built houses for myself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17338E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17338E\"></sup> and planted vineyards.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17338F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17338F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I made gardens and parks and planted all kinds of fruit trees in them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I made reservoirs to water groves of flourishing trees.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I bought male and female slaves and had other slaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17341G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17341G\"></sup> who were born in my house. I also owned more herds and flocks than anyone in Jerusalem before me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I amassed silver and gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17342H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17342H\"></sup> for myself, and the treasure of kings and provinces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17342I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17342I\"></sup> I acquired male and female singers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17342J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17342J\"></sup> and a harem as well—the delights of a man’s heart.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I became greater by far than anyone in Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17343K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17343K\"></sup> before me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17343L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17343L\"></sup> In all this my wisdom stayed with me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I denied myself nothing my eyes desired;I refused my heart no pleasure.My heart took delight in all my labor,and this was the reward for all my toil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Yet when I surveyed all that my hands had doneand what I had toiled to achieve,everything was meaningless, a chasing after the wind;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17345M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17345M\"></sup>nothing was gained under the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17345N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17345N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then I turned my thoughts to consider wisdom,and also madness and folly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17346O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17346O\"></sup>What more can the king’s successor dothan what has already been done?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17346P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17346P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I saw that wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17347Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17347Q\"></sup> is better than folly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17347R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17347R\"></sup>just as light is better than darkness.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The wise have eyes in their heads,while the fool walks in the darkness;but I came to realizethat the same fate overtakes them both.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17348S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17348S\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then I said to myself,“The fate of the fool will overtake me also.What then do I gain by being wise?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17349T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17349T\"></sup>I said to myself,“This too is meaningless.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the wise, like the fool, will not be long remembered;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17350U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17350U\"></sup>the days have already come when both have been forgotten.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17350V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17350V\"></sup>Like the fool, the wise too must die!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17350W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17350W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So I hated life, because the work that is done under the sun was grievous to me. All of it is meaningless, a chasing after the wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17351X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17351X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I hated all the things I had toiled for under the sun, because I must leave them to the one who comes after me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17352Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17352Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And who knows whether that person will be wise or foolish?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17353Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17353Z\"></sup> Yet they will have control over all the fruit of my toil into which I have poured my effort and skill under the sun. This too is meaningless.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So my heart began to despair over all my toilsome labor under the sun.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For a person may labor with wisdom, knowledge and skill, and then they must leave all they own to another who has not toiled for it. This too is meaningless and a great misfortune.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>What do people get for all the toil and anxious striving with which they labor under the sun?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17356AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17356AA\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All their days their work is grief and pain;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17357AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17357AB\"></sup> even at night their minds do not rest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17357AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17357AC\"></sup> This too is meaningless.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>A person can do nothing better than to eat and drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17358AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17358AD\"></sup> and find satisfaction in their own toil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17358AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17358AE\"></sup> This too, I see, is from the hand of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17358AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17358AF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>for without him, who can eat or find enjoyment?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17359AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17359AG\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To the person who pleases him, God gives wisdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17360AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17360AH\"></sup> knowledge and happiness, but to the sinner he gives the task of gathering and storing up wealth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17360AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17360AI\"></sup> to hand it over to the one who pleases God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17360AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17360AJ\"></sup> This too is meaningless, a chasing after the wind."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>There is a time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17361A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17361A\"></sup> for everything,and a season for every activity under the heavens:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to be born and a time to die,a time to plant and a time to uproot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17362B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17363C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17363C\"></sup> and a time to heal,a time to tear down and a time to build,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to weep and a time to laugh,a time to mourn and a time to dance,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to scatter stones and a time to gather them,a time to embrace and a time to refrain from embracing,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to search and a time to give up,a time to keep and a time to throw away,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to tear and a time to mend,a time to be silent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17367D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17367D\"></sup> and a time to speak,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a time to love and a time to hate,a time for war and a time for peace.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What do workers gain from their toil?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17369E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17369E\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I have seen the burden God has laid on the human race.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17370F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17370F\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He has made everything beautiful in its time.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17371G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17371G\"></sup> He has also set eternity in the human heart; yet no one can fathom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17371H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17371H\"></sup> what God has done from beginning to end.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17371I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17371I\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I know that there is nothing better for people than to be happy and to do good while they live.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>That each of them may eat and drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17373J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17373J\"></sup> and find satisfaction<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17373K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17373K\"></sup> in all their toil—this is the gift of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17373L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17373L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I know that everything God does will endure forever; nothing can be added to it and nothing taken from it. God does it so that people will fear him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17374M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17374M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Whatever is has already been,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17375N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17375N\"></sup>and what will be has been before;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17375O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17375O\"></sup>and God will call the past to account.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I saw something else under the sun:In the place of judgment—wickedness was there,in the place of justice—wickedness was there.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I said to myself,“God will bring into judgment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17377P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17377P\"></sup>both the righteous and the wicked,for there will be a time for every activity,a time to judge every deed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17377Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17377Q\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I also said to myself, “As for humans, God tests them so that they may see that they are like the animals.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17378R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17378R\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Surely the fate of human beings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17379S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17379S\"></sup> is like that of the animals; the same fate awaits them both: As one dies, so dies the other. All have the same breath; humans have no advantage over animals. Everything is meaningless.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All go to the same place; all come from dust, and to dust all return.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17380T\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Who knows if the human spirit rises upward<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17381U\"></sup> and if the spirit of the animal goes down into the earth?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So I saw that there is nothing better for a person than to enjoy their work,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17382V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17382V\"></sup> because that is their lot.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17382W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17382W\"></sup> For who can bring them to see what will happen after them?"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Again I looked and saw all the oppression<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17383A\"></sup> that was taking place under the sun:I saw the tears of the oppressed—and they have no comforter;power was on the side of their oppressors—and they have no comforter.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17383B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And I declared that the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17384C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17384C\"></sup>who had already died,are happier than the living,who are still alive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17384D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17384D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But better than bothis the one who has never been born,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17385E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17385E\"></sup>who has not seen the evilthat is done under the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17385F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17385F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And I saw that all toil and all achievement spring from one person’s envy of another. This too is meaningless, a chasing after the wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17386G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17386G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Fools fold their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17387H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17387H\"></sup>and ruin themselves.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Better one handful with tranquillitythan two handfuls with toil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17388I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17388I\"></sup>and chasing after the wind.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Again I saw something meaningless under the sun:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>There was a man all alone;he had neither son nor brother.There was no end to his toil,yet his eyes were not content<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17390J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17390J\"></sup> with his wealth.“For whom am I toiling,” he asked,“and why am I depriving myself of enjoyment?”This too is meaningless—a miserable business!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Two are better than one,because they have a good return for their labor:",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If either of them falls down,one can help the other up.But pity anyone who fallsand has no one to help them up.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Also, if two lie down together, they will keep warm.But how can one keep warm alone?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Though one may be overpowered,two can defend themselves.A cord of three strands is not quickly broken.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Better a poor but wise youth than an old but foolish king who no longer knows how to heed a warning.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The youth may have come from prison to the kingship, or he may have been born in poverty within his kingdom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I saw that all who lived and walked under the sun followed the youth, the king’s successor.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>There was no end to all the people who were before them. But those who came later were not pleased with the successor. This too is meaningless, a chasing after the wind."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Guard your steps when you go to the house of God. Go near to listen rather than to offer the sacrifice of fools, who do not know that they do wrong.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Do not be quick with your mouth,do not be hasty in your heartto utter anything before God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17400A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17400A\"></sup>God is in heavenand you are on earth,so let your words be few.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17400B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17400B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A dream<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17401C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17401C\"></sup> comes when there are many cares,and many words mark the speech of a fool.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17401D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17401D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When you make a vow to God, do not delay to fulfill it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17402E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17402E\"></sup> He has no pleasure in fools; fulfill your vow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17402F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17402F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is better not to make a vow than to make one and not fulfill it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17403G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17403G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do not let your mouth lead you into sin. And do not protest to the temple messenger, “My vow was a mistake.” Why should God be angry at what you say and destroy the work of your hands?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Much dreaming and many words are meaningless. Therefore fear God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17405H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17405H\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If you see the poor oppressed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17406I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17406I\"></sup> in a district, and justice and rights denied, do not be surprised at such things; for one official is eyed by a higher one, and over them both are others higher still.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The increase from the land is taken by all; the king himself profits from the fields.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whoever loves money never has enough;whoever loves wealth is never satisfied with their income.This too is meaningless.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As goods increase,so do those who consume them.And what benefit are they to the ownersexcept to feast their eyes on them?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sleep of a laborer is sweet,whether they eat little or much,but as for the rich, their abundancepermits them no sleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17410J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17410J\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I have seen a grievous evil under the sun:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17411K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17411K\"></sup>wealth hoarded to the harm of its owners,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>or wealth lost through some misfortune,so that when they have childrenthere is nothing left for them to inherit.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Everyone comes naked from their mother’s womb,and as everyone comes, so they depart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17413L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17413L\"></sup>They take nothing from their toil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17413M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17413M\"></sup>that they can carry in their hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17413N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17413N\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This too is a grievous evil:As everyone comes, so they depart,and what do they gain,since they toil for the wind?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17414O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17414O\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All their days they eat in darkness,with great frustration, affliction and anger.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This is what I have observed to be good: that it is appropriate for a person to eat, to drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17416P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17416P\"></sup> and to find satisfaction in their toilsome labor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17416Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17416Q\"></sup> under the sun during the few days of life God has given them—for this is their lot.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moreover, when God gives someone wealth and possessions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17417R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17417R\"></sup> and the ability to enjoy them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17417S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17417S\"></sup> to accept their lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17417T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17417T\"></sup> and be happy in their toil—this is a gift of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17417U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17417U\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They seldom reflect on the days of their life, because God keeps them occupied with gladness of heart.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17418V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17418V\"></sup>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>I have seen another evil under the sun, and it weighs heavily on mankind:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>God gives some people wealth, possessions and honor, so that they lack nothing their hearts desire, but God does not grant them the ability to enjoy them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17420A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17420A\"></sup> and strangers enjoy them instead. This is meaningless, a grievous evil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17420B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17420B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A man may have a hundred children and live many years; yet no matter how long he lives, if he cannot enjoy his prosperity and does not receive proper burial, I say that a stillborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17421C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17421C\"></sup> child is better off than he.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17421D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17421D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It comes without meaning, it departs in darkness, and in darkness its name is shrouded.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Though it never saw the sun or knew anything, it has more rest than does that man—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>even if he lives a thousand years twice over but fails to enjoy his prosperity. Do not all go to the same place?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17424E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17424E\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Everyone’s toil is for their mouth,yet their appetite is never satisfied.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17425F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17425F\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>What advantage have the wise over fools?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17426G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17426G\"></sup>What do the poor gainby knowing how to conduct themselves before others?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Better what the eye seesthan the roving of the appetite.This too is meaningless,a chasing after the wind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17427H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17427H\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whatever exists has already been named,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17428I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17428I\"></sup>and what humanity is has been known;no one can contendwith someone who is stronger.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The more the words,the less the meaning,and how does that profit anyone?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For who knows what is good for a person in life, during the few and meaningless days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17430J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17430J\"></sup> they pass through like a shadow?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17430K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17430K\"></sup> Who can tell them what will happen under the sun after they are gone?"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>A good name is better than fine perfume,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17431A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17431A\"></sup>and the day of death better than the day of birth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17431B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17431B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is better to go to a house of mourningthan to go to a house of feasting,for death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17432C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17432C\"></sup> is the destiny<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17432D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17432D\"></sup> of everyone;the living should take this to heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Frustration is better than laughter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17433E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17433E\"></sup>because a sad face is good for the heart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The heart of the wise is in the house of mourning,but the heart of fools is in the house of pleasure.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17434F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17434F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is better to heed the rebuke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17435G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17435G\"></sup> of a wise personthan to listen to the song of fools.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Like the crackling of thorns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17436H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17436H\"></sup> under the pot,so is the laughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17436I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17436I\"></sup> of fools.This too is meaningless.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Extortion turns a wise person into a fool,and a bribe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17437J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17437J\"></sup> corrupts the heart.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The end of a matter is better than its beginning,and patience<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17438K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17438K\"></sup> is better than pride.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not be quickly provoked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17439L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17439L\"></sup> in your spirit,for anger resides in the lap of fools.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17439M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17439M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Do not say, “Why were the old days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17440N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17440N\"></sup> better than these?”For it is not wise to ask such questions.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Wisdom, like an inheritance, is a good thing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17441O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17441O\"></sup>and benefits those who see the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17441P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17441P\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Wisdom is a shelteras money is a shelter,but the advantage of knowledge is this:Wisdom preserves those who have it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Consider what God has done:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17443Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17443Q\"></sup>Who can straightenwhat he has made crooked?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17443R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17443R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When times are good, be happy;but when times are bad, consider this:God has made the oneas well as the other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17444S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17444S\"></sup>Therefore, no one can discoveranything about their future.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In this meaningless life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17445T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17445T\"></sup> of mine I have seen both of these:the righteous perishing in their righteousness,and the wicked living long in their wickedness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17445U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17445U\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Do not be overrighteous,neither be overwise—why destroy yourself?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Do not be overwicked,and do not be a fool—why die before your time?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17447V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17447V\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It is good to grasp the oneand not let go of the other.Whoever fears God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17448W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17448W\"></sup> will avoid all extremes.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17449X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17449X\"></sup> makes one wise person more powerful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17449Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17449Y\"></sup>than ten rulers in a city.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Indeed, there is no one on earth who is righteous,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17450Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17450Z\"></sup>no one who does what is right and never sins.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17450AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17450AA\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Do not pay attention to every word people say,or you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17451AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17451AB\"></sup> may hear your servant cursing you—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for you know in your heartthat many times you yourself have cursed others.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All this I tested by wisdom and I said,“I am determined to be wise”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17453AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17453AC\"></sup>—but this was beyond me.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Whatever exists is far off and most profound—who can discover it?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17454AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17454AD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So I turned my mind to understand,to investigate and to search out wisdom and the scheme of things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17455AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17455AE\"></sup>and to understand the stupidity of wickednessand the madness of folly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17455AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17455AF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I find more bitter than deaththe woman who is a snare,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17456AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17456AG\"></sup>whose heart is a trapand whose hands are chains.The man who pleases God will escape her,but the sinner she will ensnare.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17456AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17456AH\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Look,” says the Teacher,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17457AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17457AI\"></sup> “this is what I have discovered:“Adding one thing to another to discover the scheme of things—",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>while I was still searchingbut not finding—I found one upright man among a thousand,but not one upright woman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17458AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17458AJ\"></sup> among them all.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>This only have I found:God created mankind upright,but they have gone in search of many schemes.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Who is like the wise?Who knows the explanation of things?A person’s wisdom brightens their faceand changes its hard appearance.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Obey the king’s command, I say, because you took an oath before God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Do not be in a hurry to leave the king’s presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17462A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17462A\"></sup> Do not stand up for a bad cause, for he will do whatever he pleases.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Since a king’s word is supreme, who can say to him, “What are you doing?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17463B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17463B\"></sup>”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Whoever obeys his command will come to no harm,and the wise heart will know the proper time and procedure.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For there is a proper time and procedure for every matter,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17465C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17465C\"></sup>though a person may be weighed down by misery.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Since no one knows the future,who can tell someone else what is to come?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As no one has power over the wind to contain it,so no one has power over the time of their death.As no one is discharged in time of war,so wickedness will not release those who practice it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All this I saw, as I applied my mind to everything done under the sun. There is a time when a man lords it over others to his own hurt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then too, I saw the wicked buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17469D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17469D\"></sup>—those who used to come and go from the holy place and receive praise in the city where they did this. This too is meaningless.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When the sentence for a crime is not quickly carried out, people’s hearts are filled with schemes to do wrong.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Although a wicked person who commits a hundred crimes may live a long time, I know that it will go better<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17471E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17471E\"></sup> with those who fear God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17471F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17471F\"></sup> who are reverent before him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17471G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17471G\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet because the wicked do not fear God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17472H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17472H\"></sup> it will not go well with them, and their days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17472I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17472I\"></sup> will not lengthen like a shadow.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There is something else meaningless that occurs on earth: the righteous who get what the wicked deserve, and the wicked who get what the righteous deserve.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17473J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17473J\"></sup> This too, I say, is meaningless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17473K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17473K\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So I commend the enjoyment of life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17474L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17474L\"></sup>, because there is nothing better for a person under the sun than to eat and drink<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17474M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17474M\"></sup> and be glad.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17474N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17474N\"></sup> Then joy will accompany them in their toil all the days of the life God has given them under the sun.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When I applied my mind to know wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17475O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17475O\"></sup> and to observe the labor that is done on earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17475P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17475P\"></sup>—people getting no sleep day or night—",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>then I saw all that God has done.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17476Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17476Q\"></sup> No one can comprehend what goes on under the sun. Despite all their efforts to search it out, no one can discover its meaning. Even if the wise claim they know, they cannot really comprehend it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17476R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17476R\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>So I reflected on all this and concluded that the righteous and the wise and what they do are in God’s hands, but no one knows whether love or hate awaits them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17477A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17477A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All share a common destiny—the righteous and the wicked, the good and the bad, the clean and the unclean, those who offer sacrifices and those who do not.As it is with the good,so with the sinful;as it is with those who take oaths,so with those who are afraid to take them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17478B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17478B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>This is the evil in everything that happens under the sun: The same destiny overtakes all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17479C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17479C\"></sup> The hearts of people, moreover, are full of evil and there is madness in their hearts while they live,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17479D\"></sup> and afterward they join the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17479E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17479E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Anyone who is among the living has hope—even a live dog is better off than a dead lion!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the living know that they will die,but the dead know nothing;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17481F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17481F\"></sup>they have no further reward,and even their name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17481G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17481G\"></sup> is forgotten.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17481H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17481H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Their love, their hateand their jealousy have long since vanished;never again will they have a partin anything that happens under the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17482I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17482I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Go, eat your food with gladness, and drink your wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17483J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17483J\"></sup> with a joyful heart,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17483K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17483K\"></sup> for God has already approved what you do.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Always be clothed in white,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17484L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17484L\"></sup> and always anoint your head with oil.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Enjoy life with your wife,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17485M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17485M\"></sup> whom you love, all the days of this meaningless life that God has given you under the sun—all your meaningless days. For this is your lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17485N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17485N\"></sup> in life and in your toilsome labor under the sun.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whatever<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17486O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17486O\"></sup> your hand finds to do, do it with all your might,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17486P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17486P\"></sup> for in the realm of the dead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17486Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17486Q\"></sup> where you are going, there is neither working nor planning nor knowledge nor wisdom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17486R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17486R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I have seen something else under the sun:The race is not to the swiftor the battle to the strong,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17487S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17487S\"></sup>nor does food come to the wise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17487T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17487T\"></sup>or wealth to the brilliantor favor to the learned;but time and chance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17487U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17487U\"></sup> happen to them all.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17487V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17487V\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Moreover, no one knows when their hour will come:As fish are caught in a cruel net,or birds are taken in a snare,so people are trapped by evil times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17488W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17488W\"></sup>that fall unexpectedly upon them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17488X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17488X\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I also saw under the sun this example of wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17489Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17489Y\"></sup> that greatly impressed me:",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>There was once a small city with only a few people in it. And a powerful king came against it, surrounded it and built huge siege works against it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now there lived in that city a man poor but wise, and he saved the city by his wisdom. But nobody remembered that poor man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17491Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17491Z\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I said, “Wisdom is better than strength.” But the poor man’s wisdom is despised, and his words are no longer heeded.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17492AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17492AA\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The quiet words of the wise are more to be heededthan the shouts of a ruler of fools.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Wisdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17494AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17494AB\"></sup> is better than weapons of war,but one sinner destroys much good."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>As dead flies give perfume a bad smell,so a little folly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17495A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17495A\"></sup> outweighs wisdom and honor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The heart of the wise inclines to the right,but the heart of the fool to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Even as fools walk along the road,they lack senseand show everyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17497B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17497B\"></sup> how stupid they are.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If a ruler’s anger rises against you,do not leave your post;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17498C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17498C\"></sup>calmness can lay great offenses to rest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17498D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17498D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>There is an evil I have seen under the sun,the sort of error that arises from a ruler:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Fools are put in many high positions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17500E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17500E\"></sup>while the rich occupy the low ones.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I have seen slaves on horseback,while princes go on foot like slaves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17501F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17501F\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Whoever digs a pit may fall into it;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17502G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17502G\"></sup>whoever breaks through a wall may be bitten by a snake.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17502H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17502H\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Whoever quarries stones may be injured by them;whoever splits logs may be endangered by them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17503I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17503I\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If the ax is dulland its edge unsharpened,more strength is needed,but skill will bring success.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If a snake bites before it is charmed,the charmer receives no fee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17505J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17505J\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Words from the mouth of the wise are gracious,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17506K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17506K\"></sup>but fools are consumed by their own lips.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17506L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17506L\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>At the beginning their words are folly;at the end they are wicked madness—",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>and fools multiply words.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17508M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17508M\"></sup>No one knows what is coming—who can tell someone else what will happen after them?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17508N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17508N\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The toil of fools wearies them;they do not know the way to town.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Woe to the land whose king was a servant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17510O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17510O\"></sup>and whose princes feast in the morning.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Blessed is the land whose king is of noble birthand whose princes eat at a proper time—for strength and not for drunkenness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17511P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17511P\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Through laziness, the rafters sag;because of idle hands, the house leaks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17512Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17512Q\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A feast is made for laughter,wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17513R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17513R\"></sup> makes life merry,and money is the answer for everything.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Do not revile the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17514S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17514S\"></sup> even in your thoughts,or curse the rich in your bedroom,because a bird in the sky may carry your words,and a bird on the wing may report what you say."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Ship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17515A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17515A\"></sup> your grain across the sea;after many days you may receive a return.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17515B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17515B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Invest in seven ventures, yes, in eight;you do not know what disaster may come upon the land.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If clouds are full of water,they pour rain on the earth.Whether a tree falls to the south or to the north,in the place where it falls, there it will lie.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Whoever watches the wind will not plant;whoever looks at the clouds will not reap.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As you do not know the path of the wind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17519C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17519C\"></sup>or how the body is formed in a mother’s womb,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17519D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17519D\"></sup>so you cannot understand the work of God,the Maker of all things.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Sow your seed in the morning,and at evening let your hands not be idle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17520E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17520E\"></sup>for you do not know which will succeed,whether this or that,or whether both will do equally well.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Light is sweet,and it pleases the eyes to see the sun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17521F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17521F\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>However many years anyone may live,let them enjoy them all.But let them remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17522G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17522G\"></sup> the days of darkness,for there will be many.Everything to come is meaningless.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You who are young, be happy while you are young,and let your heart give you joy in the days of your youth.Follow the ways of your heartand whatever your eyes see,but know that for all these thingsGod will bring you into judgment.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17523H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17523H\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So then, banish anxiety<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17524I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17524I\"></sup> from your heartand cast off the troubles of your body,for youth and vigor are meaningless.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17524J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17524J\"></sup>"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17525A\"></sup> your Creatorin the days of your youth,before the days of trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17525B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17525B\"></sup> comeand the years approach when you will say,“I find no pleasure in them”—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>before the sun and the lightand the moon and the stars grow dark,and the clouds return after the rain;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>when the keepers of the house tremble,and the strong men stoop,when the grinders cease because they are few,and those looking through the windows grow dim;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>when the doors to the street are closedand the sound of grinding fades;when people rise up at the sound of birds,but all their songs grow faint;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17528C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17528C\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>when people are afraid of heightsand of dangers in the streets;when the almond tree blossomsand the grasshopper drags itself alongand desire no longer is stirred.Then people go to their eternal home<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17529D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17529D\"></sup>and mourners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17529E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17529E\"></sup> go about the streets.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Remember him—before the silver cord is severed,and the golden bowl is broken;before the pitcher is shattered at the spring,and the wheel broken at the well,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and the dust returns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17531F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17531F\"></sup> to the ground it came from,and the spirit returns to God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17531G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17531G\"></sup> who gave it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17531H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17531H\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Meaningless! Meaningless!” says the Teacher.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17532I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17532I\"></sup>“Everything is meaningless!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17532J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17532J\"></sup>”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Not only was the Teacher wise, but he also imparted knowledge to the people. He pondered and searched out and set in order many proverbs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17533K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17533K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The Teacher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17534L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17534L\"></sup> searched to find just the right words, and what he wrote was upright and true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17534M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17534M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The words of the wise are like goads, their collected sayings like firmly embedded nails<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17535N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17535N\"></sup>—given by one shepherd.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Be warned, my son, of anything in addition to them.Of making many books there is no end, and much study wearies the body.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17536O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17536O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now all has been heard;here is the conclusion of the matter:Fear God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17537P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17537P\"></sup> and keep his commandments,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17537Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17537Q\"></sup>for this is the duty of all mankind.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17537R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17537R\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For God will bring every deed into judgment,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17538S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17538S\"></sup>including every hidden thing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-17538T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-17538T\"></sup>whether it is good or evil."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;